title: For Sale:  Custom, Attorney Drafted NFA Gun Trust
postcontent: I am a Florida licensed attorney and offer comprehensive NFA gun trust drafting services. My trusts are 20+ pages and cover the numerous issues related to NFA items for you and your beneficiaries. A gun trust enables you to purchase suppressors, short barreled rifles and fully automatic rifles without the hassles (and often impossibility) of a chief law enforcement officer signature as well as other bureaucratic red tape. As a firearms enthusiast, I want to see more people enjoying the benefits of NFA items and, because this isn't my primary source of income, I can offer my services at $199 for a trust. This includes an initial in-person or phone consultation to determine how to best serve your needs, all fees and documents, an electronic copy of your final trust documents, a guide to how to best use your trust as well as an appendix of ATF advisory letters and forms. While there are cheaper “fill-in-the-blank” trusts available online, the ATF has given negative feedback on many of these as not being well drafted and having the potential to expose the user to criminal and civil penalties. Not only am I licensed and in good standing in Florida, but I am also licensed and in good standing in Arkansas and Texas and can assist with trusts in those states as well. I prefer cash, but am willing to accept trades of equivalent value at my discretion. Please contact me, David Kronenfeld, at 2ndamendmenttrusts@gmail.com to inquire about my services.

postcontent: I went to the range today and shot my Smith & Wesson 44 magnum. The first group was noteworthy, but subsequent efforts were less satisfactory. The recoil was getting to me.So, I have for sale a beautiful Smith and Wesson Model 629-3 Classic Hunter. The 629-3 Classic Hunter was a limited issue run of 2000 guns produced 1991. A Smith & Wesson expert will tell you that the -3 and -4 models are the most desired by model 629 shooters.
